Commentary Text: McClenaghan to Warner, out Lbw!! And he strikes first ball! What a great asset he has been for Mumbai Indians this season. This is a big, big wicket and a wicket that Mumbai needed badly. Warner was on the back foot expecting some short stuff, wasn't to be. McClenaghan spears in a full one that keeps tailing in to hit Warner on the back pad. Dead in front. Warner was looking to play straight...oh wait! Snicko shows that he seem to have got a faint inside edge on that. Warner lbw b McClenaghan 6(6) [4s-1]
